make fun of him.

01:05.298 --> 01:06.800
- I'm not gonna
make fun of him.

01:06.866 --> 01:07.967
I'm happy for him.

01:08.034 --> 01:09.502
Uah, oh.

01:09.569 --> 01:10.737
- Ha! Busted!

01:10.804 --> 01:12.305
- Congratulations!

01:12.372 --> 01:16.376
Ugh?

01:16.443 --> 01:18.978
- Uh, hey, guys.

01:19.045 --> 01:21.614
- That's one weird
looking girlfriend.

01:21.681 --> 01:24.584
- ♪

01:32.492 --> 01:35.495
- So, wait, you've been out here
meeting with a rock?

01:35.562 --> 01:37.730
- Yep, I like rocks.

01:37.797 --> 01:38.932
- But why are
you talking to it?

01:38.998 --> 01:42.068
- Because I'm we-e-e-eird.

01:42.135 --> 01:43.903
- Uh, makes sense to me.

01:43.970 --> 01:46.973
- Mm, it looks like
a really big finger.

01:47.040 --> 01:48.541
- Oh, yeah, it's a finger rock.

01:48.608 --> 01:51.110
- I've never seen
anything like it before.

01:51.177 --> 01:52.612
I think it's cool.

01:52.679 --> 01:54.214
Plus it's an index finger.

01:54.280 --> 01:56.216
That's my favorite finger.

01:56.282 --> 01:58.084
But you guys already know that.

01:58.151 --> 02:01.221
- Also, you can pick
your nose with it, like this.

02:01.287 --> 02:03.389
Ugh!

02:03.456 --> 02:05.458
Owww!

02:05.525 --> 02:07.894
- I think we should
give it a name.

02:07.961 --> 02:10.562
- Let's call him
Fatty Fat Garbage Face.

02:10.630 --> 02:11.965
- Hmm, no.

02:12.031 --> 02:13.433
He looks like an Ira.

02:13.500 --> 02:14.667
Ira Fingerman.

02:14.734 --> 02:16.302
- I'm sitting on Ira's head.

02:16.369 --> 02:18.505
- All right, enough
with the cool dumb finger.

02:18.571 --> 02:20.640
Dade's mom threw out
a bunch of eggs this morning.

02:20.707 --> 02:23.109
I wanna see how many
I can eat before I barf.

02:23.176 --> 02:26.279
- Yeah, you can do it, Fee!

02:26.346 --> 02:28.481
- Well, it was nice
meeting ya, Ira.

02:33.820 --> 02:36.623
- FEE: Harvey, come on.

02:36.689 --> 02:37.857
- ♪

02:37.924 --> 02:39.492
- [owl hoots]

02:39.559 --> 02:42.562
- Man, that cat
sure does love lasagna.

02:42.629 --> 02:46.065
- [thunder rumbles]

02:51.504 --> 02:55.575
- ♪

03:00.213 --> 03:02.549
- [splash]

03:02.615 --> 03:06.085
- ♪

03:13.526 --> 03:15.094
- Oooh, ooh.

03:15.161 --> 03:17.797
Oh, I really didn't
think this through.

03:17.864 --> 03:21.401
- ♪

03:24.571 --> 03:26.639
- You are alive.

03:26.706 --> 03:28.474
So what are you?

03:28.541 --> 03:32.178
You can't be
just a finger, right?

03:32.245 --> 03:36.149
Are you attached
to something or--or someone?

03:36.215 --> 03:39.319
How did you even get here?

03:39.385 --> 03:42.155
- ♪

03:48.227 --> 03:51.698
- Ha, you're welcome.

03:51.764 --> 03:55.635
It must not be a lot of fun
being stuck under there.

03:55.702 --> 03:58.605
- ♪

04:00.273 --> 04:01.507
- [cart squeaking]

04:01.574 --> 04:05.612
- You guys, Ira Fingerman
is alive.

04:05.678 --> 04:06.980
- BOTH: Whoa!

04:07.046 --> 04:08.014
- I know.

04:08.081 --> 04:09.215
We gotta find out
more about him.

04:09.282 --> 04:11.651
Like what he is
or why he's there.

04:11.718 --> 04:14.721
- Harvey, do you think Ira's
insides are made of ice cream?

04:14.787 --> 04:15.755
- Maybe.

04:15.822 --> 04:17.423
I mean, I don't
know, probably not.

04:17.490 --> 04:20.093
All right, I'm gonna see
if the library has any books

04:20.159 --> 04:21.728
on giant fingers.

04:21.793 --> 04:23.029
- Cool.

04:23.096 --> 04:24.597
Me and Foo are gonna stay here
and build a book fort.

04:24.664 --> 04:25.765
- Cool.

04:25.832 --> 04:27.900
And, remember, let's
keep this to ourselves.

04:27.967 --> 04:29.936
Ready? Break.

04:30.003 --> 04:31.504
- ♪

04:31.571 --> 04:33.006
- Harvey, what are you doing?

04:33.072 --> 04:34.507
- Oh, hey, mom.

04:34.574 --> 04:37.210
Do you know if there are any
books about giant living fingers

04:37.276 --> 04:38.511
made of stone?

04:38.578 --> 04:42.115
- Sweetie, do I look like
some kind of nerd?

04:42.181 --> 04:44.751
- You look like a librarian.

04:44.817 --> 04:47.086
- Oh there, let's cool
it with the labels, kiddo.

04:47.153 --> 04:50.923
Yeah, maybe a librarian would
tell you that you probably

04:50.990 --> 04:52.125
shouldn't look in this section.

04:52.191 --> 04:53.526
This is a pregnancy book.

04:53.593 --> 04:54.961
Let me just put this away.

04:55.028 --> 04:55.795
Ha!

04:55.862 --> 04:59.098
- [crash]

04:59.165 --> 05:01.100
- Anyway, maybe you don't
need to know

05:01.167 --> 05:02.869
what your rock friend is.

05:02.935 --> 05:04.504
It's like your dad's cooking.

05:04.570 --> 05:08.241
He says its food, but
you really have no clue.

05:08.307 --> 05:10.276
- Yeah, that's true.

05:10.343 --> 05:12.412
I guess I just wanna make
sure he's okay down there.

05:12.478 --> 05:14.747
- Why don't we dig him up
and see for ourselves?

05:14.814 --> 05:16.683
- Foo, that's brilliant.

05:16.749 --> 05:17.750
- BOTH: Yeah!

05:17.817 --> 05:19.085
- High fives!

05:19.152 --> 05:21.521
- Up top.

05:21.587 --> 05:23.122
- Uh. Uh.

05:23.189 --> 05:25.024
- Uh. Uh.
- Ha!

05:25.091 --> 05:27.093
- Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha!

05:27.160 --> 05:28.394
- Uh.
- Uh.

05:28.461 --> 05:30.029
- Ha!
- Uh.

05:30.096 --> 05:32.031
- Uh.
- Ha.

05:32.098 --> 05:33.733
- Ha.

05:33.800 --> 05:34.801
- [clap]

05:34.867 --> 05:36.135
- [clap]

05:36.202 --> 05:37.637
- [clap]

05:37.704 --> 05:39.172
- [clap]

05:39.238 --> 05:40.707
- [clap]

05:40.773 --> 05:42.408
- [clap]

05:44.377 --> 05:49.015
- Oh, man, Ira's gonna
be so psyched when we--huh?

05:49.082 --> 05:53.720
- [laughing]

05:53.786 --> 05:57.056
- [laughs]

05:57.123 --> 05:57.924
- What?

05:57.990 --> 05:59.292
What's going on?

05:59.358 --> 06:02.528
I thought Ira was a secret
only we were supposed to know.

06:02.595 --> 06:04.497
- Yeah, that's why
I told everyone

06:04.564 --> 06:11.037
so they know he's a secret, too.

06:11.104 --> 06:13.106
- This is my--ah!

06:13.172 --> 06:13.940
- Uh.

06:14.006 --> 06:16.242
Yee-haw! Uh! Uh!

06:16.309 --> 06:18.044
Ah!

06:18.111 --> 06:19.345
- Stop it!

06:19.412 --> 06:20.780
You guys can't do this!

06:20.847 --> 06:22.882
You're not respecting
the finger!

06:22.949 --> 06:23.916
Ugh!

06:23.983 --> 06:25.051
- I'm not gonna
respect that thing.

06:25.118 --> 06:26.486
Who knows what its touched.

06:26.552 --> 06:28.020
- He's not a thing, Dade!

06:28.087 --> 06:29.489
He has a name!

06:29.555 --> 06:31.023
- I don't like your tone.

06:31.090 --> 06:32.091
- Sorry.

06:32.158 --> 06:34.060
- Wait. He has a name.

06:34.127 --> 06:36.162
- Yes, his name
is Ira Fingerman.

06:36.229 --> 06:38.898
And he's alive, and
he has feelings.

06:38.965 --> 06:41.534
I mean, how would you feel if
you were stuck in the ground,

06:41.601 --> 06:44.537
not able to play
or move or talk?

06:44.604 --> 06:50.042
What if Ira wants to get out of
there, but he can't tell us?

06:50.109 --> 06:51.878
You guys, we've gotta help him.

06:51.944 --> 06:52.912
- You heard the man.

06:52.979 --> 06:54.113
Get diggin'.

06:54.180 --> 06:55.681
- ALL: Ow!

06:55.748 --> 06:57.350
- ♪

06:57.416 --> 07:00.987
- [grunting]

07:03.890 --> 07:07.026
- Ira's gonna be so happy
when we get him out.

07:07.093 --> 07:10.163
He'll be able to run and jump
and feel the grass

07:10.229 --> 07:13.499
between his toes...if he has
toes.

07:13.566 --> 07:15.368
- DADE'S THOUGHTS: Oh,
no, Harvey, you fool.

07:15.434 --> 07:19.372
Don't you know weird things
are bad news?

07:19.438 --> 07:25.378
- [rumbling]

07:25.444 --> 07:26.646
- Aaah!

07:26.712 --> 07:28.347
- Aaah!

07:28.414 --> 07:29.749
- HARVEY: Dade!

07:29.816 --> 07:31.617
Grab my hand!

07:31.684 --> 07:34.387
- But, Harvey, what about
Fee and Foo?

07:34.453 --> 07:36.255
- I never liked
them as much as you.

07:36.322 --> 07:37.590
- Oh my gosh, Harvey.

07:37.657 --> 07:39.926
- It's a good thing we dug up
that finger,

07:39.992 --> 07:44.030
because it reminded me what
an awesome dude you are to me.

07:44.096 --> 07:47.266
[echoes] To me, to me, to me.

07:47.333 --> 07:50.670
Uh ma gosh, out of my way!

07:50.736 --> 07:54.173
Ugh, ugh, kick it in gear,
you bunch of lazy Susans!

07:54.240 --> 07:57.376
- ALL: [grunting]

08:01.280 --> 08:03.883
- [panting]
Yo, man, I can't do this.

08:03.950 --> 08:04.784
Uh.

08:04.851 --> 08:06.319
- We've been digging for hours.

08:06.385 --> 08:08.654
- My wand is tired!

08:08.721 --> 08:11.290
- I'm not sure if we're getting
any closer to the bottom of him.

08:11.357 --> 08:13.025
All I see is more digit.

08:13.092 --> 08:13.893
- Doesn't matter.

08:13.960 --> 08:15.261
We have to keep going.

08:15.328 --> 08:18.064
Everyone just pretend you're
doing something really fun.

08:18.130 --> 08:19.298
What's something you like doing?

08:19.365 --> 08:20.533
- Not digging.

08:20.600 --> 08:22.501
- Well, just think of that
and keep digging.

08:22.568 --> 08:25.004
- [thunder rumbles]

08:25.071 --> 08:29.141
- ALL: [groaning]

08:29.208 --> 08:31.844
- [wind gushing]

08:31.911 --> 08:34.280
- ♪

08:34.347 --> 08:37.216
- Oh, stupid wind,
get over yourself.

08:37.283 --> 08:39.652
Ugh, ugh, aaah!

08:39.719 --> 08:42.255
- Guys, just stay strong.

08:42.321 --> 08:43.856
- [tree cracking]

08:43.923 --> 08:45.224
- [crash]

08:45.291 --> 08:46.259
- Whoa!

08:46.325 --> 08:47.360
- Ah!

08:47.426 --> 08:50.162
- Aah!

08:50.229 --> 08:51.330
- Ugh!

08:51.397 --> 08:53.432
Uh, uh, uh.

08:53.499 --> 08:55.801
Oh, ah.

09:01.474 --> 09:04.243
- ALL: [groaning]

09:04.310 --> 09:06.145
- Oh no!

09:06.212 --> 09:09.582
All of our hard word is ruined!

09:09.649 --> 09:11.584
- Well, we'll just start over.

09:11.651 --> 09:13.920
And--and we'll work
a thousand times faster.

09:13.986 --> 09:16.155
As long as we stay focused,
we should be able to--

09:16.222 --> 09:18.057
- You guys, you gotta see this!

09:18.124 --> 09:21.260
The wind blew me into a rock
that looks just like a butt!

09:21.327 --> 09:22.428
- Oh, I gotta see that.

09:22.495 --> 09:23.562
- [indistinct chatter]

09:23.629 --> 09:25.131
- Wait, guys, no!

09:25.197 --> 09:28.367
We have to...keep digging.

09:28.434 --> 09:29.635
- You coming, dude?

09:29.702 --> 09:31.771
- I can't leave Ira.

09:31.837 --> 09:35.942
You just go look at
the butt rock for me.

09:36.008 --> 09:39.645
- ♪

09:40.446 --> 09:45.151
- Uh, uh, uh, uh, uh, uh.

09:45.217 --> 09:46.385
- There he is.

09:46.452 --> 09:49.121
He's still going.

09:49.188 --> 09:50.656
- Uh, uh.
- Hey, son.

09:50.723 --> 09:51.657
- Hey, mom, can't talk now.

09:51.724 --> 09:54.360
I gotta dig up Ira.

09:54.427 --> 10:00.032
- Well, here, let
me give you a hand.

10:00.099 --> 10:02.101
Look, I know it's frustrating
to face something

10:02.168 --> 10:03.703
you can't quite figure out.

10:03.769 --> 10:06.172
Maybe Ira's place in the forest
isn't something you or I

10:06.238 --> 10:10.876
would want for ourselves,
but...we aren't Ira.

10:10.943 --> 10:13.412
Maybe this is where
Ira's supposed to be.

10:13.479 --> 10:14.981
Maybe not.

10:15.047 --> 10:17.850
But you know you really did
a good thing trying to help him.

10:17.917 --> 10:20.319
Some things
are just too big for us.

10:20.386 --> 10:23.089
And that's okay.

10:23.155 --> 10:26.025
- Ira, is it okay?

10:26.092 --> 10:29.695
- ♪

10:36.202 --> 10:38.637
- HARVEY: Okay, I'm
ready to go home now.

10:38.704 --> 10:40.906
- I'm proud of you, Harvey.

10:40.973 --> 10:43.976
- ♪

10:50.783 --> 10:53.652
- Hey, Ira, we got a bunch
of really great stuff

10:53.719 --> 10:55.121
for you to touch today.

10:55.187 --> 10:56.422
Yarn.

10:56.489 --> 10:57.757
Marbles.

10:57.823 --> 10:59.959
And something super special.

11:00.026 --> 11:01.794
Bubble wrap!

11:01.861 --> 11:03.596
- And I brought this guy.

11:03.662 --> 11:05.097
- What? Where am I?

11:05.164 --> 11:06.465
- He's pretty squishy.

11:06.532 --> 11:08.034
Harvey, go long!

11:08.100 --> 11:08.701
- Oh, man!

11:08.768 --> 11:11.837
- BOTH: [laughing]

11:17.810 --> 11:20.012
- [crickets chirping]
- ♪

11:20.079 --> 11:21.147
- DAD: All ready
for bed, champ?

11:21.213 --> 11:21.914
- HARVEY: Yep.

11:21.981 --> 11:23.249
Is the front door locked?

11:23.315 --> 11:24.884
- DAD: You betcha, son.

11:24.950 --> 11:26.318
- Is my nightlight on?

11:26.385 --> 11:27.787
- Always is.

11:27.853 --> 11:31.257
- And could you leave
the ceiling light on as well?

11:31.323 --> 11:35.394
- You want your nightlight
and the ceiling light on?

11:35.461 --> 11:38.064
- [yawns]

11:38.130 --> 11:40.199
Yeah.

11:40.266 --> 11:45.805
Hey, guys, do you think that I
could...be a magical...

11:45.871 --> 11:49.642
garbage man some day?

11:49.708 --> 11:50.776
- Good night, Harvey.

11:50.843 --> 11:54.513
- Don't get up again.

11:54.580 --> 11:57.083
- Fee, hurry up!

11:57.149 --> 11:59.485
- FEE: [humming]

11:59.552 --> 12:00.319
Ready for bed, bro?

12:00.386 --> 12:02.588
- Ready.

12:02.655 --> 12:04.557
I feel like a little baby.

12:04.623 --> 12:05.591
- Want your nightlight on?

12:05.658 --> 12:08.661
- Yeah.

12:08.727 --> 12:10.262
I made a drawing for you.

12:10.329 --> 12:13.099
It's under my head.

12:13.165 --> 12:14.100
- [laughs]

12:14.166 --> 12:15.468
That's so sweet.

12:15.534 --> 12:16.735
Oh!

12:16.802 --> 12:18.604
[laughing]

12:18.671 --> 12:23.209
- BOTH: [laughing]

12:25.411 --> 12:26.512
- FOO: Ugh!

12:26.579 --> 12:27.913
- FEE: Sorry, dude!

12:27.980 --> 12:31.117
- BOTH: [laughing]

12:31.183 --> 12:32.418
- Good night.
- Good night.

12:32.485 --> 12:33.419
- Good night.
- Good night.

12:33.486 --> 12:34.420
- Good night.
- Good night.

12:34.487 --> 12:35.321
- Good night.
- Good night.

12:35.387 --> 12:36.222
- Good night.
- Good night.

12:36.288 --> 12:37.490
- Good night.
- Good night.

12:37.556 --> 12:39.391
- Good night.
- Good night.

12:39.458 --> 12:40.726
- Good night Foo.

12:40.793 --> 12:42.661
- Good night, sis.

12:42.728 --> 12:45.898
- ♪

12:54.807 --> 12:57.710
- BOTH: [laughing] Oh!

12:57.776 --> 12:59.178
[laughing] Oh!

12:59.245 --> 13:00.479
[laughing]

13:00.546 --> 13:03.749
- Boy, it's nice to hike
together just the three of us.

13:03.816 --> 13:05.451
- Hey, we're hungry.

13:05.518 --> 13:06.452
- Yeah!

13:06.519 --> 13:07.720
- I got granola.

13:07.786 --> 13:08.921
I got kale chips.

13:08.988 --> 13:12.424
I got lots of sandwiches,
baby carrots, um,

13:12.491 --> 13:16.362
cut-up strawberries, veggie
chips, some mini pretzels.

13:16.428 --> 13:18.898
Ugh, ugh.

13:18.964 --> 13:20.799
I--I'm not sure what happened.

13:20.866 --> 13:21.767
- Whoa.

13:21.834 --> 13:23.235
Look what Harvey's doing.

13:23.302 --> 13:25.538
- FOO: I think he's scratching
his back on the rock.

13:25.604 --> 13:27.006
- Like a bear.

13:27.072 --> 13:29.408
- No fair, I wanna be a bear.

13:29.475 --> 13:31.810
- [struggling]

13:33.646 --> 13:35.014
Huh?

13:35.080 --> 13:37.650
I think this metal on backpack
is sticking to this rock.

13:37.716 --> 13:39.652
I think these rocks
might be magnetic.

13:39.718 --> 13:40.886
- [electricity zapping]

13:40.953 --> 13:42.855
- Can't hear you, Harvey, we're
being bears.

13:42.922 --> 13:45.658
- Oh, I--I don't know if
you should be doing that.

13:45.724 --> 13:46.926
- What kind of
sandwich is that?

13:46.992 --> 13:48.761
- Uh, peanut butter and honey.

13:48.827 --> 13:51.597
- Bears love honey.

13:51.664 --> 13:53.465
- Oh no you don't,
I'm a bear, too.

13:53.532 --> 13:54.466
- Ah!

13:54.533 --> 13:55.701
Hmm?

13:55.768 --> 13:57.703
- ♪

13:57.770 --> 14:00.139
- Ah!

14:00.206 --> 14:01.874
- Hey!

14:01.941 --> 14:04.577
- Ah! Whoa!

14:04.643 --> 14:07.012
Oah!

14:07.079 --> 14:08.847
- What the heck, man?

14:08.914 --> 14:09.982
- [struggling]

14:10.049 --> 14:11.917
I think I know what's going on.

14:11.984 --> 14:13.819
I think those are load stones,

14:13.886 --> 14:15.788
which is kind of
like a magnetic rock.

14:15.854 --> 14:17.523
And when you and Foo rubbed up
against 'em,

14:17.590 --> 14:19.091
you got magnetized, too.

14:19.158 --> 14:20.693
- What are you guys
talking about?

14:20.759 --> 14:23.362
- You see, when you have
two magnets that have the same

14:23.429 --> 14:26.532
charge, they push each other
apart, like this.

14:26.599 --> 14:28.167
[struggling]

14:28.234 --> 14:33.372
- So...if I get close to Foo,
he'll get pushed away.

14:33.439 --> 14:34.707
Aaah!

14:34.773 --> 14:35.808
- I got out of the tree.

14:35.874 --> 14:36.842
What's wrong with us?

14:36.909 --> 14:38.611
- Harvey says we're magnetized.

14:38.677 --> 14:39.945
- Awesome!

14:40.012 --> 14:41.213
- [laughs]

14:41.280 --> 14:44.216
- I wonder how bad
this is for your bones.

14:44.283 --> 14:45.484
- Ooh-wee!

14:45.551 --> 14:47.419
Ooh-wee!

14:47.486 --> 14:48.787
Ooh-wee!

14:48.854 --> 14:50.522
- [laughing]

14:50.589 --> 14:53.325
Hey, Harvey!

14:53.392 --> 14:54.360
- Wow.

14:54.426 --> 14:56.629
- [laughs]

14:56.695 --> 15:00.266
- Ready, Foo?

15:00.332 --> 15:01.100
Whoo!

15:01.166 --> 15:02.134
- BOTH: [laughing]

15:02.201 --> 15:03.469
- Hey, let me spin you.

15:03.535 --> 15:05.471
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!

15:05.537 --> 15:06.572
[laughs]

15:06.639 --> 15:07.840
- [bell ringing]

15:07.906 --> 15:09.275
- Oh, boy, lunch!

15:09.341 --> 15:11.577
- ♪

15:11.644 --> 15:12.745
- Hurry up, Fee.

15:12.811 --> 15:14.480
[humming]

15:14.546 --> 15:15.814
Whoa!

15:15.881 --> 15:17.549
- Oh, oops.

15:17.616 --> 15:19.285
- Don't worry, I'm okay.

15:21.487 --> 15:22.921
Oh, right.

15:22.988 --> 15:27.559
- Oh, I guess I'll
go wait outside.

15:27.626 --> 15:29.161
Oh.

15:29.228 --> 15:30.729
- ♪

15:30.796 --> 15:33.332
- [slurping]

15:39.405 --> 15:41.440
- [chewing]

15:41.507 --> 15:42.441
- I don't like this.

15:42.508 --> 15:43.475
This is dumb.

15:43.542 --> 15:44.777
- Foo's right.

15:44.843 --> 15:47.279
So, what, we like can't eat
lunch together anymore?

15:47.346 --> 15:49.048
- Oh, man.

15:49.114 --> 15:50.816
And what about breakfast?

15:50.883 --> 15:54.486
And dinner?

15:54.553 --> 15:57.489
- All right, Harvey,
I'm done being magnetized.

15:57.556 --> 15:58.624
Can you fix us?

15:58.691 --> 16:00.392
- Gee, I don't know how.

16:00.459 --> 16:04.263
But I know someone who knows
a lot about science.

16:04.330 --> 16:06.832
Mr. Moth, sir, can you
please help my friends?

16:06.899 --> 16:09.568
- The affliction that plagues
them is much too powerful

16:09.635 --> 16:12.104
for I, a mere gizmologist.

16:12.171 --> 16:13.539
- Why are you
talking like that?

16:13.605 --> 16:18.544
- Younglings, perhaps you've
never heard of Steampunk,

16:18.610 --> 16:22.314
the sci-fi subculture that
perfectly marries Victorian

16:22.381 --> 16:26.785
technology and light, gears
and watches and stuff.

16:26.852 --> 16:28.120
People think it's cool.

16:28.187 --> 16:31.056
- [slurps]
Ha, that is not cool, dude.

16:31.123 --> 16:33.959
- A-a-all right, kids are mean.

16:34.026 --> 16:36.228
- Hey, wait, you gotta help us.

16:36.295 --> 16:38.530
I think Steampunk
is really cool.

16:38.597 --> 16:39.298
- You do?

16:39.365 --> 16:41.233
- Of course, I really do.

16:41.300 --> 16:44.269
So do you think there's
any way you can help my friends?

16:44.336 --> 16:49.341
- Well...behold the power
of static electricity.

16:52.010 --> 16:52.845
- [electricity zapping]

16:52.911 --> 16:54.346
- Dim--dim the lights, please?

16:54.413 --> 16:56.315
- Um? Oh.

16:56.382 --> 16:58.484
- It's possible that a static
electric shock

16:58.550 --> 17:02.187
of incredible magnitude
could return your friends

17:02.254 --> 17:04.857
to their natural polarity.

17:04.923 --> 17:07.492
But that would
probably kill them!

17:07.559 --> 17:08.660
- [crash]

17:08.727 --> 17:09.895
- [gasps] Kill them?

17:09.962 --> 17:11.230
- Good luck.

17:11.296 --> 17:13.999
- Harvey, so what are
we going to do to fix this?

17:14.066 --> 17:17.269
- Uh, I don't think we can.

17:17.336 --> 17:20.305
- ♪

17:20.372 --> 17:22.741
- Okay, Foo, I'm
going to tuck you into bed

17:22.808 --> 17:24.542
from over here tonight.

17:24.609 --> 17:28.480
Uh, uh, come on, uh.

17:28.547 --> 17:30.382
Uh.

17:30.449 --> 17:31.283
- Ah!

17:31.350 --> 17:32.584
Oh!

17:32.651 --> 17:34.586
- Sorry, dude.

17:34.653 --> 17:35.687
Are you asleep?

17:35.754 --> 17:37.189
- I can't hear you.

17:37.256 --> 17:38.657
This is awful.

17:38.724 --> 17:42.961
- I know it's tough, but we
gotta figure this out ourselves.

17:43.028 --> 17:46.465
- BOTH: Harvey!

17:46.532 --> 17:48.500
- [groans]

17:48.567 --> 17:49.635
- Foo can't sleep.

17:49.701 --> 17:51.470
You have to tuck him in.

17:51.537 --> 17:54.640
- And you have to do it
exactly like Fee does.

17:54.706 --> 17:56.008
You know what that means?

17:56.074 --> 17:57.309
- What does that mean?

17:57.376 --> 17:58.677
- Kiss my head, Harvey.

17:58.744 --> 17:59.978
You have to do it.

18:00.045 --> 18:01.380
You have to kiss my head.

18:01.447 --> 18:02.648
- No.

18:02.714 --> 18:04.616
I don't wanna do that.

18:04.683 --> 18:06.485
- Kiss my head!

18:06.552 --> 18:07.820
- Mmmm.

18:07.886 --> 18:09.655
- [laughs]

18:09.721 --> 18:11.490
Send that to Fee.

18:15.828 --> 18:17.396
- This is from Foo.

18:17.463 --> 18:21.500
Uh.

18:21.567 --> 18:22.668
- Did you get it?

18:22.734 --> 18:23.936
- [sighs]

18:24.002 --> 18:26.905
It's just not the same.

18:26.972 --> 18:28.340
Send him one of these.

18:28.407 --> 18:30.275
- Hmm?

18:30.342 --> 18:34.680
Okay. See you guys tomorrow.

